neither the temples of my head to take ány rést; 5 Until I find out a place for the temple óf the LÓRD;
an habitation for the Mighty Gód of Jácob. 6 Lo, we heard of the sáme at Ephrátah,
and found it ín the woód. 7 We will go into his tábernácle,
and fall low on our knees befóre his foótstool. 8 Arise, O LORD, into thy résting-pláce;
thou, and the árk of thy stréngth. 9 Let thy priests be clothed with ríghteousnéss;
and let thy saints sing with jóyfulnéss. 10 For thy servant Dávid’s sáke,
turn not away the face of thíne anoínted. 11 The LORD hath made a faithful oath únto Dávid,
and he shall not shrínk from ít: 12 Of the fruít of thy bódy
shall I set upón thy thróne. 13 If thy children will keep my covenant, and my testimonies that Í shall teách them;
their children also shall sit upon thy throne forévermóre. 14 For the LORD hath chosen Sion to be an habitation fór himsélf;
he hath lónged for hér. 15 This shall be my rést foréver:
here will I dwell, for I have a delíght thereín. 16 I will bless her victuáls with íncrease,
and will satisfy her poór with breád. 17 I will deck her priésts with heálth,
